TITLE: Creating a Git Repository in Azure DevOps with Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a new Git repository within an Azure DevOps project using Terraform. It includes the creation of the project and the repository with initialization settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/terraform-provider-azuredevops/blob/main/website/docs/r/git_repository.html.markdown#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
resource "azuredevops_project" "example" {
  name               = "Example Project"
  visibility         = "private"
  version_control    = "Git"
  work_item_template = "Agile"
}

resource "azuredevops_git_repository" "example" {
  project_id     = azuredevops_project.example.id
  name           = "Example Git Repository"
  default_branch = "refs/heads/main"
  initialization {
    init_type = "Clean"
  }
  lifecycle {
    ignore_changes = [
      initialization,
    ]
  }
}
```

