TITLE: Retrieving Git Repository Information in Azure DevOps using Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the azuredevops_git_repository data source to retrieve information about a specific Git repository within an Azure DevOps project. It first retrieves the project ID and then uses it to fetch details of a named repository.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/terraform-provider-azuredevops/blob/main/website/docs/d/git_repository.html.markdown#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
data "azuredevops_project" "example" {
  name = "Example Project"
}

# Load a specific Git repository by name
data "azuredevops_git_repository" "example-single-repo" {
  project_id = data.azuredevops_project.example.id
  name       = "Example Repository"
}
```

